history.content:
This schedule is fine. Many students take 61B and 70 together. Data 100 is not a very heavy class. It has weekly programming hw assignments and 2 projects.

Student Response 2: You might want to hold off on taking 70 with 61B. If you are taking 61B during the fall, Hilfinger is known to give tough projects. Also, if you don't have much mathematical experience with probability or discrete math, making 70 your only "high-stakes" class makes sense because it requires a lot of time commitment from students who don't have that much of a mathematical scaffolding as others. 

Response 3: Do note that Hilfinger's projects aren't much worse than Hug's. In fact, Hug's projects these last few semesters have been far harder than some of the previous Hilfinger projects.
